The Presidential candidate of Peoples Democratic Party, Atiku Abubakar, has said that he would accept whatever outcome of 2019 election if the entire process is adjudged by all to be free, fair and credible when asked what he will do if he lost. Atiku said this on Wednesday evening at The Candidate, a political forum where he and his vice presidential running mate, Peter Obi, were engaged in a question and answer conversation conducted by Khadaria Ahmed. He also said that he had lost elections in the past and had respected the results.